A case of attempted murder has been opened at the Durban North SAPS after a woman was shot at The Pearls of Umhlanga hotel. A video surfaced on social media of awoman being shot by an unknown gunman in the parking area of the Pearls of Umhlanga Hotel, north of Durban. Police spokesperson, Lieutenant Colonel Nqobile Gwala, said police responded to a report of a shooting at a hotel in Umhlanga on Sunday at 1.30 pm. “Upon their arrival at the said place, the 25-year-old victim had been rushed to hospital after sustaining a gunshot wound to the neck," Gwala said that the suspects fled the scene in their getaway vehicle, but were later apprehended. "A 25-year-old suspect was arrested. His firearm was also seized by the police, and he appeared in the Verulam Magistrates' court [on Monday]," added Gwala. The motive for the shooting is still unknown.